The analysis of thymocytes revealed no significant difference in the percentages of CD4+CD8−subsets between lyp/lyp, lyp/+ and +/+ F344 rats. CD4−CD8+T cells were increased (ANOVA=0.044) in the lyp/lyp compared to the +/+ F344 rats (Table 2
). However there was a reduction of CD4+CD8+(P=0.02) and an increase of CD4−CD8−(P=0.033) T cells in the lyp/lyp compared to that of +/+ F344 rats. The alpha-beta TCR subset was reduced in lyp/lyp compared to the +/+ F344 rats (P=0.016) but no difference was found for CD90+and CD3+T cells (Table 2and Fig. 3
).
